</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="92.[136,779,717,1356]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,298,887,913]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Remarks</emphasis>
. The key features of the genus, as diagnosed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Illg" box="[296,420,921,948]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, are the combination of a 9- to 10-segmented antennule of the female, the 2-segmented maxilliped bearing 9 and 2 setae on proximal and distal segments, respectively, the presence of setiform elements (rather than spines) on outer margins of the posterior swimming legs, and the reduction of the fifth leg to two setiform papillae. 
<bibRefCitation author="Illg" box="[342,464,1125,1152]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg (1958)</bibRefCitation>
designated his new species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[136,298,1159,1185]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Pygodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilonaris">
<emphasis box="[136,298,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. aquilonaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[393,441,1160,1186]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[582,725,1159,1185]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Pygodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[582,725,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Pygodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and transferred three other species from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1859" box="[576,699,1194,1219]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,699,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Doropygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schellenberg, 1922)" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1922" class="Ascidiacea" family="Corellidae" genus="Corella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. antarctica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A." box="[279,515,1227,1253]" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="217 - 274" part="10" refId="ref330676" refString="Schellenberg, A. (1922) Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 10 (2), 217 - 274. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 4830100201" title="Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten" type="journal article" year="1922">Schellenberg, 1922</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schellenberg, 1922)" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1922" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Pygodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novaeseelandiae">
<emphasis box="[549,778,1227,1253]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. novaeseelandiae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A." box="[144,370,1261,1287]" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="217 - 274" part="10" refId="ref330676" refString="Schellenberg, A. (1922) Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 10 (2), 217 - 274. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 4830100201" title="Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten" type="journal article" year="1922">Schellenberg, 1922</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schellenberg, 1922)" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1922" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Pygodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellipes">
<emphasis box="[450,600,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. lamellipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A." journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="217 - 274" part="10" refId="ref330676" refString="Schellenberg, A. (1922) Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 10 (2), 217 - 274. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 4830100201" title="Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten" type="journal article" year="1922">Schellenberg, 1922</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Afifth species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stock, 1967" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" box="[418,716,1295,1322]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Pygodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patriciae">
<emphasis box="[418,435,1296,1321]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[457,558,1296,1321]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">patriciae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, J. H." box="[572,716,1295,1321]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was added later by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, J. H." box="[302,450,1329,1356]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock (1967)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
